 'Tis true she tel's me; I love your wit well Sir;  
but I must
cut my coat according to my cloath.

 Will good Landlady set on the Pot, as they say;  
or make
the Jack goe; then I'll hear you.

 I hope I shall have your good word too Madam, to   
your
Cousin for me;

 I'll tell you Madam, it has upon it a very fair    
Manor house;
from one side you have in prospect an hanging Garden.

 If you will needs know, the name's Bawdy ;     
sure this will give
a stop to their curiosity.

 Mr. Burr , I owe you not that satisfaction;  
what you have
heard you may interpret as you please.

 A good Estate, that makes every thing handsome;  
nothing
can look well without it.
